    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-06-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-06-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="755"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d755">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/2000.</note>
                <head>[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-06-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 9, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 59.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: Referring to your note of the 20th ultimo,
                    in regard to a report that 12 Mexican Federal employees who had been driven from
                    Tia Juana were being detained by the local authorities of San Diego, Cal., and
                    that 3 of them had been molested there, by sympathizers with filibusters, I have
                    the honor to inclose herewith for your information a copy of a letter from the
                    Attorney General,<note n="1" xml:id="d755fn1">Not printed.</note> stating that
                    he has instructed the United States attorney at Los Angeles to take such steps
                    in the matter as may be appropriate.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
